        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Many Nashville hosts start by cleaning their own properties. It seems economical. It rarely works long-term.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Burnout is Real</h3>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Cleaning is physical work. Doing it between every booking while also managing guest communications, maintenance, restocking, and your actual job? It's not sustainable.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          By month three, you're rushing. By month six, you're cutting corners. By month nine, you get that bad review.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">You Can't Be Objective</h3>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          It's your place. You stop seeing things. That small stain on the carpet? You know it's there, so your brain edits it out. Guests don't.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Availability Problems</h3>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          What happens when you're sick? On vacation? Have a family emergency? Your bookings don't stop. You need reliable coverage.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Finding the Right Cleaning Partner</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          For Nashville Airbnb hosts, the right cleaning company isn't just a vendor—they're a partner in your business success. Here's what to look for:
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Short-Term Rental Experience</h3>

