          <li>Liability insurance (we carry $2 million)</li>
          <li>Background-checked staff</li>
          <li>Professional processes and accountability</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">The Cost of Bad Cleaning vs. Good Cleaning</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Let's do the math for a typical Nashville Airbnb:
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>Average nightly rate:</strong> $175<br>
          <strong>Average booking:</strong> 3 nights<br>
          <strong>Revenue per booking:</strong> $525
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>One bad cleanliness review impacts:</strong>
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-8 space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-600">
          <li>Search ranking drop = fewer bookings for 3-6 months</li>
          <li>Conversion rate drop = people who view don't book</li>
          <li>Conservative estimate: 2-4 lost bookings</li>
          <li>Revenue impact: $1,050-$2,100</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          <strong>Cost of professional cleaning:</strong> $85-$175 per turnover
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          The math is clear. Professional cleaning isn't an expense—it's insurance for your rental income.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Nashville Neighborhoods We Serve</h2>

